        // OOP Concept ın Java  -- Object Oriented Programming

        // Java is Object Oriented -- It is about flexiblity, having more functions and to do operations through the objects


        // Keywords: parent, child, super, extend


        // 1) Single İnheritance  -->  clas A extends  class B   // class B is parent, class A is child

        // 2) Multi Level Inheritance --> clas A extends --> class B --> extends class C
                                        // sub classes: A,B.  parent classes: B, C grand parent: C
                                        // class A is the richest one


        // 3) hierarhical inheritance
                    // class A extends X
                    // class B extends X
                    // class C extends X


        // Phone  --> parent
        // iphone , samsung, TCL  --> sub classes



        Is this possible ? --> NO --> Since multiple inheritance is not allowed in Java
        // class A extends class B
        // class A extends class C

        // one child can have only one mother
        // multiple inheritance is not allowed in java





